82 template <typename Array, bool Alias>
83 class TsrExpr : public Expr<TsrExpr<Array, Alias> > {
84  public:
85  typedef TsrExpr<Array, Alias> TsrExpr_;
86  typedef Expr<TsrExpr_> Expr_;
87  typedef
88  typename ExprTrait<TsrExpr_>::array_type array_type;
89  typedef typename ExprTrait<TsrExpr_>::engine_type
90  engine_type;
91 
92  private:
93  array_type& array_;
94  std::string vars_;
95 
96  public:
97  // Compiler generated functions
98  TsrExpr() = default;
99  TsrExpr(const TsrExpr_&) = default;
100  TsrExpr(TsrExpr_&&) = default;
101  ~TsrExpr() = default;
102 
104 
107  TsrExpr(array_type& array, const std::string& vars)
108  : array_(array), vars_(vars) {}
109 
111 
113  array_type& operator=(TsrExpr_& other) {
114  other.eval_to(*this);
115  return array_;
116  }
117 
119 
122  template <typename D>
123  array_type& operator=(const Expr<D>& other) {
124  static_assert(
125  TiledArray::expressions::is_aliased<D>::value,
126  "no_alias() expressions are not allowed on the right-hand side of "
127  "the assignment operator.");
128  other.derived().eval_to(*this);
129  return array_;
130  }
131 
133 
136  template <typename D>
137  array_type& operator+=(const Expr<D>& other) {
138  static_assert(
139  TiledArray::expressions::is_aliased<D>::value,
140  "no_alias() expressions are not allowed on the right-hand side of "
141  "the assignment operator.");
142  return operator=(AddExpr<TsrExpr_, D>(*this, other.derived()));
143  }
144 
146 
149  template <typename D>
150  array_type& operator-=(const Expr<D>& other) {
151  static_assert(
152  TiledArray::expressions::is_aliased<D>::value,
153  "no_alias() expressions are not allowed on the right-hand side of "
154  "the assignment operator.");
155  return operator=(SubtExpr<TsrExpr_, D>(*this, other.derived()));
156  }
157 
159 
162  template <typename D>
163  array_type& operator*=(const Expr<D>& other) {
164  static_assert(
165  TiledArray::expressions::is_aliased<D>::value,
166  "no_alias() expressions are not allowed on the right-hand side of "
167  "the assignment operator.");
168  return operator=(MultExpr<TsrExpr_, D>(*this, other.derived()));
169  }

174  array_type& array() const { return array_; }
